POPULAR comedian, TV personality and YouTube sensation Moshe Ndiki is elated at the prospect of hosting the red carpet ahead of the Miss South Africa pageant set to happen on 13 August 2022 at the SunBet Arena at Time Square, Pretoria. Ndiki expressed gratitude and detailed how this opportunity is a dream come true for him.  “I am super ecstatic to be this year’s Miss South Africa red carpet host! It is an honour to be a part of the Miss South Africa legacy. This is truly a blessing and a dream transformed into reality. There’s something beautiful about making dreams come true and on August 13 we will be making a young person’s dream become a reality by crowning her Miss South Africa 2022,” said Ndiki. He added, “I am expecting nothing but the finest red carpet looks from our celebrity guests who’ll be gracing us on the evening, so those at home should expect everything that is glitz and glam.” The Eastern Cape-born and -bred entertainer has amassed more than a million views on YouTube and has a huge following on social media. The chief executive of the Miss SA Organisation, Stephanie Weil said they were elated to have Ndiki on board.  “We’re thrilled to have Moshe host our red carpet and welcome VIP guests to our glittering, entertainment packed event. He provides a sense of glamour and of fun which kicks off proceedings with punch.” Award-winning media personality Anele Mdoda was also excited after being announced as the host of the pageant. “I am very excited that we are back to a full capacity arena, because a packed arena suits my energy levels and always motivates me to work just that little bit harder to ensure that everyone has a good time and really enjoys the evening,” Mdoda said. Both the red carpet coverage, pageant finale, and interview with the newly crowned Miss South Africa will be live streamed exclusively on the Miss South Africa app. You can download the Miss South Africa App for free from the Apple App Store or Google Play store.